================================================================
PRACTICAL NO. 7 - WINDOW ACTIVITIES, CONTROLS & MOUSE/KEYBOARD IN UIPATH
================================================================

PRE-REQUISITES:
- UiPath Studio installed
- A simple application open (Notepad works perfectly for all parts)
- UiPath.UIAutomation.Activities package installed (usually default)

================================================================
PRACTICAL 7(a) - Implement the Attach Window Activity
================================================================

DIFFICULTY: Easy

WHAT YOU WILL DO:
You will use "Attach Window" to target an already-open application window
and perform actions inside it (type text into Notepad).

--- STEP-BY-STEP INSTRUCTIONS ---

Step 1: Open Notepad on your computer.
  - Press Windows key → type "Notepad" → press Enter
  - Leave it open (don't type anything yet)

Step 2: Open UiPath Studio → New Project.
  - Name it: Practical_7a_AttachWindow
  - Click Create

Step 3: In the Designer panel, drag an "Attach Window" activity 
        into the Main sequence.

Step 4: Click "Indicate Window on Screen" inside the Attach Window activity.
  - Your screen will dim and a blue border will appear as you hover.
  - Move your mouse over the Notepad window and LEFT CLICK on it.
  - UiPath will now remember this window as the target.

Step 5: Inside the Attach Window activity's body (the white area inside),
        drag a "Type Into" activity.
  - Click "Indicate element inside window"
  - Move mouse to the white text area of Notepad and click it.
  - In the "Text" field of Type Into, type: "Hello from UiPath Attach Window!"

Step 6: Below the Type Into, drag a "Send Hotkey" activity (still inside Attach Window).
  - Key: select "s" from the dropdown
  - Check the "Ctrl" modifier checkbox
  - This simulates Ctrl+S to save the file.

Step 7: Run the workflow (F5).
  EXPECTED RESULT: Notepad opens, the text is typed into it,
  and then Ctrl+S is pressed (a Save dialog will appear — 
  you can manually close it or add more steps to handle it).

WHY USE ATTACH WINDOW?
  - It locks your automation to a specific window.
  - Even if other windows are on top, UiPath will bring this window to focus.
  - Very useful in multi-window environments.

